'Fitness' may refer to:

* Physical fitness, a general state of good health, usually as a result of
  exercise and nutrition <!-- at the top because it is the more commonly used
  meaning -->
* Fitness (biology), an individual's ability to propagate its genes
* ''Fitness'' (magazine), a women's magazine, focusing on health and exercise
* Fitness and figure competition, a form of physique training, related to
  bodybuilding
* Fitness approximation, a method of function optimization evolutionary
  computation or artificial evolution methodologies
* Fitness function, a particular type of objective function in mathematics and
  computer science
